The paper deals with privacy and influence diffusion in online social networks, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper focuses on influence propagation in online social networks. The second likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper proposes privacy-preserving mechanisms for influence diffusion. The third likely category is cs.DB (Databases), as the paper deals with nodes' relationships in online social networks. The fourth likely category is cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), as the paper deals with social networks. The fifth likely category is cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity), as the paper deals with privacy and security in online social networks.
